{
  "texts": [
    "FiQA Task 2 addresses opinion-based question answering (QA) over financial data, where systems must answer natural language questions by retrieving relevant financial opinions and facts from a knowledge base of structured and unstructured documents (such as reports, news, and microblogs).",
    "This task requires systems to either rank relevant documents from the knowledge base or generate answers directly.",
    "Opinion-based questions require identifying entities, aspects, sentiment, and opinion holders, with performance evaluated on metrics like F-score, Normalized Discounted Cumulative Gain (NDCG), and Mean Reciprocal Rank (MRR).",
    "The QA test collection includes diverse sources like StackExchange, Reddit, and StockTwits, focusing on ranking and answering accuracy.",
    "The Zero-Shot prompt used for FiQA is given in Figure 15."
  ]
}